19
00:01:00.206 --> 00:01:03.048
by having the right product in the right amount

20
00:01:03.048 --> 00:01:05.864
on hand when needed for patient care.

21
00:01:05.864 --> 00:01:08.796
Staff can also have the Prime Vendor schedule, plan

22
00:01:08.796 --> 00:01:11.374
and supply needed items to the facility without

23
00:01:11.374 --> 00:01:14.534
overstocking or stock outages.

24
00:01:14.534 --> 00:01:18.189
For example, if real levels are set in the primary

25
00:01:18.189 --> 00:01:21.068
and secondary areas, then this will impact the true

26
00:01:21.068 --> 00:01:24.180
